Decoder todo:
- Review for memory leaks. Need a way to make sure allocated SV's are freed
  appropriately on error without using sv_2mortal on everything.
- Review for refcount leaks: Need to make sure that we arent returning things
  with artificially high refcounts.
- Related to refcount leaks: Why do regexps SvPVMG's end up with a refcount of
  two when we return? See below:

    $ make; perl -MDevel::Peek -Mblib=../Decoder/blib -Mblib=../Encoder/blib -MSereal::Encoder=encode_sereal \
                -MSereal::Decoder=decode_sereal -le'print my $enc= encode_sereal(my $o= qr/foo/); my $dump= 
                eval { decode_sereal($enc) };  Dump($dump); 0 and Dump($o); print STDERR "Got : $dump\nWant: $o\n";' \
                | perl -Mblib=../Decoder/blib -Mblib=../Encoder/blib ../Encoder/author_tools/hobodecoder.pl 
